# distil-job-feed — Memory

## 1. Purpose
A standalone job-scraping microservice for the "distil" AI CV-parsing product
(sibling repo `../distil`). Verified: both repos share an identical `Job`
Prisma model (`@@map("jobs")`, same fields/enums) and the `.env.example` here
says "same connection string as in the Distil project" — this repo writes
directly into the same Neon Postgres DB that `distil`'s Next.js app reads
from. `distil/src/app/(app)/browse/page.tsx` references job-feed jobs.
No HTTP server / API here — it's pure batch scripts that fetch external job
listings and upsert them into the shared `jobs` table for `distil` to display
and let candidates apply against.

## 2. Tech stack
- TypeScript (ES2022, ESNext modules), run via `tsx` (no compile step used)
- Prisma ORM 6.x with `@prisma/adapter-pg` (driver adapter) + `pg` Pool
- Node 20 (per CI), `dotenv` for env loading
- No framework, no HTTP server, no test runner present

## 3. Architecture / entry points
- `scripts/refresh-global.ts` — fetches Remotive, Arbeitnow, Jobicy, RemoteOK
  (all free, no API key) in parallel, upserts as `country: 'GLOBAL'`, then
  soft-expires (30-day TTL) and hard-deletes stale jobs, and sweeps old SENT
  applications to `NO_DECISION`.
- `scripts/refresh-adzuna.ts` — fetches Adzuna per active `OrgConfig.country`
  (rate-limited free tier, ~250 req/month), upserts only.
- `src/lib/feeds/{adzuna,arbeitnow,jobicy,remoteok,remotive}.ts` — one fetcher
  module per source, each normalizes to a common job shape.
- `src/lib/feeds/skills.ts` — regex keyword-matches a static ~150-term skill
  list against job descriptions to populate `requiredSkills` when a source
  doesn't provide tags.
- `prisma/schema.prisma` — `Job`, `Application`, `OrgConfig` models;
  `JobSource` enum includes `SERPAPI` but that source is explicitly commented
  as "managed by the distil repo (nightly batch) — not this repo".
- No `src/index.ts` or server entry — the two scripts are the only entry
  points (`npm run refresh-global`, `npm run refresh-adzuna`).

## 4. Deployment target
GitHub Actions only (no Vercel config, no Dockerfile, no serverless config
found):
- `.github/workflows/refresh-global.yml` — cron `*/30 * * * *` (every 30 min)
- `.github/workflows/refresh-adzuna.yml` — cron `0 2 * * *` (daily, 2am UTC)
Both run `npm ci`, `npx prisma generate`, then the relevant script, using
repo secrets `DATABASE_URL`, `ADZUNA_APP_ID`, `ADZUNA_APP_KEY`. Comments in
the scripts say this direct-DB approach "bypasses Vercel Deployment
Protection" (implying `distil` itself is Vercel-hosted, but this repo is not).

## 5. Current build/run status
- `node_modules` not installed locally; not verified to actually run
  end-to-end in this session (would require live `DATABASE_URL` +
  external API calls).
- No build/lint/test scripts defined in `package.json` (only the two
  `refresh-*` scripts). No CI step type-checks or lints before running.
- Working tree is clean, 4 commits total, in sync with `origin/main`.

## 6. Known gaps/TODOs
- No automated tests of any kind.
- No lint config despite `tsconfig.json` with `strict: true`.
- No README documenting setup for a new contributor.
- SERPAPI is a defined `JobSource` enum value but has no fetcher in this
  repo (intentionally owned by `distil` instead) — a latent coupling if the
  two repos' schemas drift.
- Adzuna quota logic assumes `OrgConfig` rows exist; falls back to hardcoded
  `IN` if none — Unclear whether this fallback is still desired behavior or
  a leftover default — needs owner input.
